::: write_speak
Why is it so hard to tell if a specific policy actually *caused* a result, or if it was just a coincidence?

::: write

### The Problem: Endogeneity

In econometrics, we often want to know if **X** causes **Y**.

::: write_speak
The trouble is "omitted variable bias." There might be a hidden factor, **Z**, that affects both your cause and your effect, making them look related when they aren't.

::: wait(click=true)

::: draw(height=200, title="The Identification Problem")
line(20,20,40,20) stroke="#888"
text(15,20,"X") fill="#60a5fa"
